      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH, mg/100L) and the derived relative hemolysis index (RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate). NIH is the accepted regulatory metric for hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance and ISO 10993-4. The RH < 1 acceptance criterion directly maps to the intended use decision: identifying whether the device produces less hemolysis than the predicate. QoI relevance is fully established."
