      "rationale": "At MRL 2, separate quantification of numerical solver error (distinct from discretization error) is not required. Solver correctness is addressed through the code verification factor (canonical benchmarks) and the discretization error factor (GCI study). Iterative convergence is monitored via residual reduction to 1e-6 for all equations; no solver divergence or oscillation observed across all 5 operating points. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
