      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/use-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal use error analysis is not required. All simulation runs were executed by trained CFD engineers following documented simulation protocols (SOP-CFD-001 Rev C). Boundary condition setup, mesh generation, and post-processing steps were independently reviewed by a second analyst. No use errors were identified during peer review. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-form-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2. The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on published literature demonstrating its suitability for rotating machinery hemolysis prediction (Hariharan et al. 2011, Garon & Farinas 2004). Sensitivity of NIH to turbulence model choice was informally assessed by comparing SST k-omega against realizable k-epsilon at the worst-case operating point; difference was 6.2%, within acceptable bounds. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-inputs-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Formal uncertainty propagation for model inputs is not required at MRL 2. Key inputs (fluid viscosity, density, pump geometry dimensions, rotational speed, inlet flow rate) are well-characterized with documented measurement uncertainties. Nominal input values are traceable to calibrated measurements. Sensitivity of NIH to ±5% variation in viscosity was assessed and found to produce <3% change in NIH. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-samples-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Statistical characterization of test sample variability is not required at MRL 2. Validation experiments used a single FDA GCBP test article with three replicate runs per operating point. Replicate variability in NIH was <4% (coefficient of variation), confirming measurement repeatability. Sample-to-sample geometric variability was not characterized, which is acceptable at MRL 2 given the use of a reference standard geometry. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/input-equivalency-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency analysis between simulation and experimental input parameters is not required at MRL 2. Simulation boundary conditions were set to match experimental test conditions: inlet velocity profiles derived from measured flow rates assuming fully developed turbulent profiles (Re > 4000 at all operating points), outlet pressure set to measured back-pressure (±50 Pa). Wall boundary conditions use no-slip with smooth wall assumption consistent with polished pump surfaces. Parameter correspondence is documented in the validation plan. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 at MRL 2."
